{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5950", "repo": "rails", "body": "> Perhaps a Model.where with no args should be chainable: Model.where.not field: nil or Model.where.like name: 'John%'\n\nI added this feature to my existing \"everywhere\" gem as a proof of concept. https://github.com/amatsuda/everywhere/compare/v1.0.1...v2.0.0\nYou can try this syntax just by adding 'everywhere' to your existing Rails 3 or 4 app's Gemfile.\n\n@jeremy \nDoes this implementation satisfy your spec?\n\n@tenderlove @jonleighton \nAnd of course I'm willing to push this feature into AR core. Any thoughts? Shall I go ahead and send a PR?", "_id": {"$oid": "523810f5bd3543c15100d72a"}, "issue_id": 5950, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6495729", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5950#issuecomment-6495729", "updated_at": "2012-06-21T22:04:05Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda", "login": "amatsuda", "gravatar_id": "76a777ff80f30bd3b390e275cce625bc", "html_url": "https://github.com/amatsuda", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/76a777ff80f30bd3b390e275cce625bc?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F76cac4685e3749728f9c04bd3a86221f.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 11493, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/amatsuda/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-06-21T22:04:05Z", "id": 6495729, "owner": "rails"}
